29. Attestation by the Buryesses qf' slyr, concerniny the yram by Alema of Lawoler, qf the Zomds (gf Dalincathe, to the Friars Preachers of ΑΨ. [aith May 1411]

Till all and syndry til quhais knawlage thir present letres sal cum the burgesses and communite of the burgh of Α111 greting in Grod everlastand : Sin meritable thing is til bere witnes til suthfastnes forthy we witnes that a nobil and wirschipful man quhilum Alane of Lawdar gase in perpetuale almous as we understand the landis of Dallincathe till the Freris Prechouris of Are for the sawle of qwhilum Alis Cambell his wyffe that liis in the hous of the Freris Prechouris beforsaid and for the sawlis of all cristin for continual prayeris of tha freris and for the anniversar of that Alis Cambell yher be yher til be done and contenuit the qwilk anniversar We witnes alsa is honestly and reverendly done in that place with speciale memore in the moneth of October as is contenyt in thar martiloge In witnes of this thing the commone seile of Are burch is set til thir present letres at Air the ferd day of the moneth of May the yer of grace a thousand four hundreth and

ellewin.
